<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>WSDL Generation has many twists between different frameworks and languages. Allowing a strategy pattern to handle the programmers preferences in which way a WSDL file should be auto-generated would be a great addition to flexibility of this component. It would allow to handle complex types based on the currently set strategy.</p>

<p>Refactoring could be done in a non BC way with implementing the current AutoDiscover mechanism as default mechanism and add additional strategies that can overwrite the default behaviour via a setter method, setDiscoverStrategy().</p>

<p>Then specific strategies that support complex types in Java Frameworks and .NET out of the box could be added.</p>

    </div>
